<subSubSection id="C3346546FFE8FFA0FF46A208FDF2517B" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B9136CDFFE8FFA0FF46A208FDF8503B" blockId="1.[151,629,1577,1599]" box="[151,629,1577,1599]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">
<taxonomicName id="4C2E4D4EFFE8FFA0FF46A208FD83503B" authority="Biesiadka, 1977" authorityName="Biesiadka" authorityYear="1977" box="[151,526,1577,1599]" class="Arachnida" family="Limnesiidae" genus="Limnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaczewskii">
<emphasis id="B95AEADFFFE8FFA0FF46A208FEEF503B" box="[151,354,1577,1599]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Limnesia jaczewskii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBF4B3CFFE8FFA0FEB9A20BFD83503B" author="Biesiadka" box="[360,526,1577,1599]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" refString="Biesiadka, E. (1977) Description de Limnesia jaczewskii sp. n. (Hydracarina). Bulletin de l'Academie Polonaise des Sciences, Serie Sciences Biologiques, Classe II, 25 (2), 89 - 94." type="journal article" year="1977">
Biesiadka, 
<number id="3DE624EAFFE8FFA0FE08A20BFD83503B" box="[473,526,1577,1599]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" value="1977.0">1977</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B95AEADFFFE8FFA0FDC9A20BFDFD503A" bold="true" box="[536,624,1577,1598]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">nov. syn</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9136CDFFE8FFA0FF46A24EFDF2517B" blockId="1.[151,1437,1644,1920]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">
According to the original description (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBF4B3CFFE8FFA0FD98A24EFD715080" author="Biesiadka" box="[585,764,1644,1669]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" refString="Biesiadka, E. (1977) Description de Limnesia jaczewskii sp. n. (Hydracarina). Bulletin de l'Academie Polonaise des Sciences, Serie Sciences Biologiques, Classe II, 25 (2), 89 - 94." type="journal article" year="1977">
Biesiadka 
<number id="3DE624EAFFE8FFA0FD10A24EFD715080" box="[705,764,1644,1668]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" value="1977.0">1977</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E4D4EFFE8FFA0FCC0A24FFC7E5080" box="[785,1011,1644,1668]" class="Arachnida" family="Limnesiidae" genus="Limnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaczewskii">
<emphasis id="B95AEADFFFE8FFA0FCC0A24FFC7E5080" box="[785,1011,1644,1668]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Limnesia jaczewskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E4D4EFFE8FFA0FB5BA24FFA8E5080" box="[1162,1283,1645,1668]" class="Arachnida" family="Limnesiidae" genus="Limnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="connata">
<emphasis id="B95AEADFFFE8FFA0FB5BA24FFA8E5080" box="[1162,1283,1645,1668]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">L. connata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in body size, the position and size of the acetabula, the shape of the palp and the attachment and number of swimming setae. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E4D4EFFE8FFA0FEE4A297FE4750C8" box="[309,458,1716,1740]" class="Arachnida" family="Limnesiidae" genus="Limnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaczewskii">
<emphasis id="B95AEADFFFE8FFA0FEE4A297FE4750C8" box="[309,458,1716,1740]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">L. jaczewskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has two posterodorsal platelets, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E4D4EFFE8FFA0FC48A297FB9850C8" box="[921,1045,1717,1740]" class="Arachnida" family="Limnesiidae" genus="Limnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="connata">
<emphasis id="B95AEADFFFE8FFA0FC48A297FB9850C8" box="[921,1045,1717,1740]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">L. connata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should have only one. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBF4B3CFFE8FFA0FF46A2F5FED450F4" author="Tuzovskij" box="[151,345,1751,1776]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" refString="Tuzovskij, P. V. (1997) Vodjaniyje klesci roda Limnesia (Acariformes, Limnesiidae) fauny rossii. Ross. Akad. Nauk, Institut Ekologii Volzskogo bassejna, Toljatti, 89 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1997">
Tuzovskij (
<number id="3DE624EAFFE8FFA0FEC7A2FAFEDD50F4" box="[278,336,1752,1776]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" value="1997.0">1997</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
showed that populations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E4D4EFFE8FFA0FD4AA2FBFC9950F4" box="[667,788,1753,1776]" class="Arachnida" family="Limnesiidae" genus="Limnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="connata">
<emphasis id="B95AEADFFFE8FFA0FD4AA2FBFC9950F4" box="[667,788,1753,1776]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">L. connata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
include specimens with both, unpaired and paired dorsal platelets. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBF4B3CFFE8FFA0FE71A2DEFDD75110" author="Biesadka" box="[416,602,1788,1813]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" refString="Biesiadka, E. (1977) Description de Limnesia jaczewskii sp. n. (Hydracarina). Bulletin de l'Academie Polonaise des Sciences, Serie Sciences Biologiques, Classe II, 25 (2), 89 - 94." type="journal article" year="1977">
Biesadka (
<number id="3DE624EAFFE8FFA0FDC6A2DEFDDF5110" box="[535,594,1788,1812]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" value="1977.0">1977</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
the palp of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E4D4EFFE8FFA0FD35A2DFFCD05110" box="[740,861,1789,1812]" class="Arachnida" family="Limnesiidae" genus="Limnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="connata">
<emphasis id="B95AEADFFFE8FFA0FD35A2DFFCD05110" box="[740,861,1789,1812]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">L. connata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be more slender, but Tuzovskij’s (
<number id="3DE624EAFFE8FFA0FAEAA2DEFAFB5110" box="[1339,1398,1788,1812]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" value="1997.0">1997</number>
) 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E4D4EFFE8FFA0FA54A2DFFF7C513C" class="Arachnida" family="Limnesiidae" genus="Limnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="connata">
<emphasis id="B95AEADFFFE8FFA0FA54A2DFFF7C513C" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">L. connata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a similar palp as 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E4D4EFFE8FFA0FDD1A303FD1E513C" box="[512,659,1824,1848]" class="Arachnida" family="Limnesiidae" genus="Limnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaczewskii">
<emphasis id="B95AEADFFFE8FFA0FDD1A303FD1E513C" box="[512,659,1824,1848]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">L. jaczewskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As no correlation can be found between these character states and body size, position and size of the acetabula and swimming setation of legs, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E4D4EFFE8FFA0FBE6A367FA935158" box="[1079,1310,1860,1884]" class="Arachnida" family="Limnesiidae" genus="Limnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaczewskii">
<emphasis id="B95AEADFFFE8FFA0FBE6A367FA935158" box="[1079,1310,1860,1884]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Limnesia jaczewskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E4D4EFFE8FFA0FDD1A34BFDF55184" box="[512,632,1897,1920]" class="Arachnida" family="Limnesiidae" genus="Limnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="connata">
<emphasis id="B95AEADFFFE8FFA0FDD1A34BFDF55184" box="[512,632,1897,1920]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">L. connata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
